<br>
One word: Casino<br>
<br>
Don't believe me?  make a lvl 1 on Vallon and port up to the bazaar, hang around there for a little while and there will be people giving casino rules shouts.<br>
<br>
Alright, the game itself is simple in conception.<br>
The rules usually used by people on Vallon are a /random 1000.  If above 600, than double the money bet, and above 800 than triple the money bet.  <br>
<br>
These rules are tweaked somewhat by individuals who run their own respective casinos, but most people stay with the &quot;if above 600 then you win&quot; rule. <br>
<br>
Also, most people use a min/max bet rule to ensure that they don't lose everything on a single roll  <br>
<br>
Some people also accept items (which they evaluate) instead of cash as bets, but this isn't very common<br>
<br>
Basically, you're gonna want to start with a healthy cred balance ..maybe about 4-5k plat to start yourself off with.<br>
<br>
Just for some  perspective, I did this last night.  Started with about 8k and walked away 4 hours later with 25k.  Its a really lucrative biz and very effortless.  <br>
<br>
Enjoy and good luck!  <br>
<br>
Dark<br>
52 Elementalist<br>
