<br>
1-600 lose<br>
601-800 2x<br>
801-1000 3x<br>
<br>
on the rolls from 1-600, better loses 600 plat (assuming 1pp per roll). on rolls 601-800, he gains back 400 (2x where x = 1). on rolls 801-1000, he gains back 600 (3x where x = 1). Therefore, the odds are definetly in the gambler's favor, not the house's. Whoever is running this thing didn't do the math correctly, or is banking on people only throwing one die and walking away.<br>
